<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/1456: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-09">September 9,
                                        1940</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>439. Your 499, 5th.<note n="60" xml:id="d220fn60">Not printed.</note>
                                After the period of active warfare Department discontinued the
                                practice of providing loans for transportation expenses for
                                Americans who have declined many opportunities afforded them for
                                return to United States. It continues willing upon receipt of names,
                                addresses and amounts desired to communicate with relatives, friends
                                or employers in United States to obtain necessary funds.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>